  "output": "Confirmed the auto-generated draft in `.claude-flow/metrics/test-gaps.json` has one bug (uses `\"type\"` instead of `\"ats\"` as the source-dict key), and it left `fetch_all`'s failure-isolation and a few CLI-routing paths unverified. I've now read every module directly. Here's the full analysis.\n\n## Current state\n\n**Zero tests exist.** No `tests/` dir, no pytest in `requirements.txt` (only `httpx`, `PyYAML`). `fetchers.py`'s own docstring says the client is \"injectable so the parsing logic is unit-testable against mocked transports\" — written to be testable, never actually tested.\n\nSetup needed:\n```\npip install pytest pytest-asyncio\n```\n`httpx.MockTransport` covers all HTTP mocking — no need for `respx`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models.py` — pure logic, highest value/cost ratio\n\nUntested: `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `.posted_dt`, `.content_hash`, `.to_row`.\n\nGaps: ms/s epoch boundary at `1e12`, negative epoch, ISO with `Z`/offset/naive, garbage prose (`\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"`) → `None` not raise, empty/`None` input, hash stability (title/location/url/department affect it, `posted_at`/`raw` don't), `to_row` drops `raw` and injects `key`/`content_hash`.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_and_none_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc and dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\").year == 2022\n\n    def test_ms_boundary_at_1e12(self):\n        # exactly 1e12 must be read as ms (~2001), not seconds (~year 33658)\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"1000000000000\").year < 3000\n\n    def test_iso8601_z_suffix(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\").tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_defaults_to_utc(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\").tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_explicit_offset_preserved(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00+05:00\")\n        assert dt.utcoffset().total_seconds() == 5 * 3600\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_negative_epoch_does_not_crash(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"-100\") is not None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **kw):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                     title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        base.update(kw)\n        return Job(**base)\n\n    def test_key_format(self):\n        assert self._job().key == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable(self):\n        assert self._job().content_hash == self._job().content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title(self):\n        assert self._job().content_hash != self._job(title=\"Sr Engineer\").content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_ignores_posted_at_and_raw(self):\n        a = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\", raw={\"a\": 1})\n        b = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-06-01\", raw={\"a\": 2})\n        assert a.content_hash == b.content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_excludes_raw_includes_key_and_hash(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": True}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n        assert \"content_hash\" in row\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `filters.py` — pure logic\n\nGaps: `\\b` word-boundary regex (`\"go\"` must not match `\"Django\"`), `exclude` beats `include`, empty-list vs `None`, case-insensitivity, **cutoff must keep undated jobs** (the single most important behavior here, explicitly a design choice), `max_age_days` as float-string, `max_age_days: 0` being falsy (`if max_age:`) silently disables the cutoff — worth locking down either as intended behavior or filing as a bug.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef make_job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Software Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\",\n                location=\"San Francisco, CA\", department=\"Engineering\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_include_word_boundary_rejects_substring(self):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"Django Developer\"), include=[\"go\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_matches_whole_word(self):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"Go Developer\"), include=[\"go\"]) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_wins_over_include(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"Senior Intern Engineer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"intern\"]) is False\n\n    def test_locations_substring_case_insensitive(self):\n        j = make_job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\")\n        assert match(j, locations=[\"francisco\"]) is True\n        assert match(j, locations=[\"seattle\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_old_dated_job(self):\n        old = make_job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30))\n                        .isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\"))\n        assert match(old, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_undated_job(self):\n        undated = make_job(posted_at=\"\")\n        assert match(undated, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)) is True\n\n    def test_special_regex_chars_escaped(self):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"C++ Engineer\"), include=[\"C++\"]) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_empty_rules_keeps_everything(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(), make_job(external_id=\"2\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n\n    def test_max_age_days_as_float_string(self):\n        old = make_job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=5))\n                        .isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\"))\n        assert filter_jobs([old], {\"max_age_days\": \"1.5\"}) == []\n\n    def test_max_age_days_zero_disables_cutoff(self):\n        # documents current behavior: `if max_age:` treats 0 as falsy\n        old = make_job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=999))\n                        .isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\"))\n        assert filter_jobs([old], {\"max_age_days\": 0}) == [old]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `store.py` — dedup correctness, the core value prop\n\nTrivially testable in-memory (`Store(\":memory:\")`). Gaps: new/unchanged/changed rows through `diff()`, the `_migrate()` additive-column path (opening a pre-`salary_range` DB), `next_seq` starting at 1 and incrementing, `added_since` strict `>` boundary and ordering, `get_meta`/`set_meta` upsert, context-manager close.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport pytest, sqlite3\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store():\n    with Store(\":memory:\") as s:\n        yield s\n\ndef make_job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_new_job_inserted_and_returned(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == [] and store.count() == 1\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_not_returned_second_run(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_changed_job_returned_in_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job(title=\"Engineer\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")])\n        assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(self, store):\n        assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\n    def test_set_meta_overwrites(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\"); store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\n    def test_next_seq_starts_at_one_and_increments(self, store):\n        assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 1\n        assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 2\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_strictly_after_ts_excludes_boundary(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        assert store.added_since(row[\"first_seen\"]) == []\n\ndef test_migration_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_schema(tmp_path):\n    db_path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(str(db_path))\n    conn.execute(\"\"\"CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT,\n        company TEXT, external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n        department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n        content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT)\"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(db_path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `notify.py` — error isolation is the key contract\n\n`dispatch()` catching per-notifier exceptions so one bad notifier (e.g. Twilio auth failure) doesn't block Slack/console is completely unguarded today.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport notify\nfrom models import Job\nfrom notify import dispatch, _sms_body\n\ndef make_job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\ndef test_dispatch_isolates_one_failing_notifier(monkeypatch):\n    calls = []\n    def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"slack down\")\n    def ok(new, changed): calls.append(\"ok\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [boom, ok])\n    dispatch([make_job()], [])\n    assert calls == [\"ok\"]\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_without_webhook_url(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    called = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"httpx.post\", lambda *a, **k: called.append(1))\n    notify.notify_slack([make_job()], [])\n    assert called == []\n\ndef test_notify_sms_noop_when_jobs_empty(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"s\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"t\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")\n    called = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"httpx.post\", lambda *a, **k: called.append(1))\n    notify.notify_sms([], [])\n    assert called == []\n\ndef test_notify_sms_raises_on_bad_creds(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"s\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"t\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")\n    class FakeResp:\n        def raise_for_status(self): raise Exception(\"401\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"httpx.post\", lambda *a, **k: FakeResp())\n    import pytest\n    with pytest.raises(Exception):\n        notify.notify_sms([make_job()], [])\n\ndef test_sms_body_truncates_at_limit_and_counts_remainder():\n    jobs = [make_job(external_id=str(i), title=f\"Job {i}\") for i in range(10)]\n    body = _sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n    assert \"+2 more\" in body\n    assert body.count(\"\\n- \") == 8\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `pipeline.py` — orchestration, the natural integration-test seam\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest, yaml\nfrom pipeline import load_config, run\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef make_job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\ndef test_load_config_defaults(tmp_path):\n    p = tmp_path / \"min.yaml\"\n    p.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = load_config(p)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {} and cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_dry_run_does_not_touch_store(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({\"sources\": [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"acme\"}],\n                                    \"db\": str(db_path)}))\n    async def fake_fetch_all(sources, concurrency): return [make_job()]\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", fake_fetch_all)\n    result = await run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n    assert not db_path.exists()\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_full_run_persists_and_dispatches(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({\"sources\": [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"acme\"}],\n                                    \"db\": str(db_path)}))\n    async def fake_fetch_all(sources, concurrency): return [make_job()]\n    dispatched = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", fake_fetch_all)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"pipeline.dispatch\", lambda new, changed: dispatched.append((new, changed)))\n    result = await run(cfg_path, dry_run=False)\n    assert result[\"new\"] == 1\n    assert dispatched[0][0][0].title == \"Engineer\"\n    assert db_path.exists()\n```\n\n(Note: config sources use the key **`ats`**, not `type` — confirmed against `fetchers.fetch_source` and `sources.yaml`.)\n\n---\n\n## 6. `fetchers.py` — largest surface, largest risk (~35 functions, 0 tests)\n\nEvery ATS integration is a hand-rolled defensive parser against an undocumented/semi-documented shape (Meta's `doc_id` rotates, Google's blob can score the wrong job, Apple/D.E.Shaw/Two Sigma/Optiver scrape raw HTML by regex). These are exactly the functions most likely to silently break on a vendor change, with zero regression protection.\n\n**`_request` retry/backoff — shared by every fetcher:**\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers.py\nimport pytest, httpx\nfrom fetchers import _request\n\ndef transport(responses):\n    it = iter(responses)\n    def handler(request):\n        status, body = next(it)\n        return httpx.Response(status, json=body, request=request)\n    return httpx.MockTransport(handler)\n\nclass TestRequestRetry:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_succeeds_first_try(self):\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport([(200, {\"ok\": True})]))\n        assert (await _request(client, \"https://x/\")).json() == {\"ok\": True}\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"fetchers.asyncio.sleep\", lambda s: None)\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport([(503, None), (200, {\"ok\": True})]))\n        assert (await _request(client, \"https://x/\")).status_code == 200\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_does_not_retry_on_404(self):\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport([(404, None)]))\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/\", retries=4)\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_exhausts_retries_and_raises(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"fetchers.asyncio.sleep\", lambda s: None)\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport([(500, None)] * 4))\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/\", retries=4)\n```\n\n**Every `parse_*` needs happy-path + empty-payload + missing-optional-field.** Template (apply to all 17 parsers — `parse_greenhouse`, `parse_lever`, `parse_ashby`(+page), `parse_smartrecruiters`, `parse_recruitee`, `parse_workable`, `parse_google`, `parse_deshaw`, `parse_twosigma`, `parse_optiver`, `parse_apple`, `parse_eightfold`, `parse_bytedance`, `parse_phenom`, `parse_meta`, `parse_microsoft`, `parse_netflix`, `parse_amazon`):\n\n```python\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_happy_path(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Engineer\", \"absolute_url\": \"https://x/1\",\n                           \"location\": {\"name\": \"Remote\"}, \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}],\n                           \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"}]}\n        from fetchers import parse_greenhouse\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert len(jobs) == 1 and jobs[0].location == \"Remote\"\n\n    def test_empty_and_missing_jobs_key(self):\n        from fetchers import parse_greenhouse\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {}) == []\n```\n\nHighest-value specific cases (encode real edge cases the code's own comments flag):\n\n| Function | Specific gap |\n|---|---|\n| `_lever_salary` | `min` only, no `max` → falls to `salaryDescriptionPlain`; both absent → `\"\"` |\n| `_ashby_salary`/`parse_ashby` | `isListed: False` jobs must be filtered out |\n| `_extract_ds1` (Google) | primary regex miss → fallback fires; malformed JSON → `[]` not a crash — this is the \"scores the wrong job\" trap; needs a synthetic multi-block HTML fixture |\n| `_ds1_posted_at` | short array (missing idx 12-14) → `\"\"`, not `IndexError` |\n| `_apple_hydration` | malformed/missing hydration script → `None`, not a crash |\n| `_amazon_posted_at` | non-\"Month D, YYYY\" string → `\"\"` not raise |\n| `_bd_location` | broken/missing `parent` chain terminates cleanly |\n| `_balanced_json` | unbalanced braces / string containing escaped quotes doesn't over/under-match |\n\n**`fetch_source`/`fetch_all` orchestration** — I read these bodies directly (`fetchers.py:1119-1147`), so this is settled, not speculative:\n- `fetch_source` raises `ValueError` on an unknown `ats` (not `KeyError`).\n- `fetch_all` **does** isolate failures — each source's coroutine is wrapped in its own `try/except Exception`, logs `\"  ! {ats}:{company} failed: {e}\"`, and returns `[]` for that source without aborting the gather.\n\n```python\nclass TestFetchSourceAndAll:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        from fetchers import fetch_source\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient()\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"not-a-real-ats\", \"company\": \"x\"})\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_one_source_failing_does_not_abort_others(self, monkeypatch):\n        from fetchers import fetch_all\n        import fetchers\n        async def fake_dispatch(client, source):\n            if source[\"company\"] == \"bad\":\n                raise RuntimeError(\"boom\")\n            return [Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"good\", external_id=\"1\",\n                        title=\"T\", url=\"https://x/1\")] if False else []\n        # simplest: monkeypatch FETCHERS entries directly\n        async def good_fetch(client, source): return []\n        async def bad_fetch(client, source): raise RuntimeError(\"boom\")\n        monkeypatch.setitem(fetchers.FETCHERS, \"greenhouse\", good_fetch)\n        monkeypatch.setitem(fetchers.FETCHERS, \"lever\", bad_fetch)\n        result = await fetch_all(\n            [{\"ats\": \"lever\", \"company\": \"bad\"}, {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"}])\n        assert result == []  # both return [], but critically no exception propagates\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. `agent.py` — CLI helpers, several sharp edges\n\n**`cmd_db_new`** (the densest logic in the repo): first-run window vs stored marker; `--posted-days` + undated job → kept unless `--dated-only`; the `dropped_old`/`undated_kept`/`undated_dropped` counters; group-boundary truncation (never splits a batch sharing one `first_seen`); `watermark` in output equals the last *fully included* group, not `since`, when truncated.\n\n**`cmd_db_mark`**: `--now`; valid ISO string; invalid string → exit `2`, stderr message, marker **not written**; neither arg → exit `2`.\n\n**`_normalize_ats`**: replacements apply only to text nodes, never inside tags/`<style>`/`<script>`; `counts` only includes labels that actually fired.\n\n**`cmd_pdf_render`**: missing input → exit `2`; success (`%PDF` magic) → exit `0`, temp file cleaned up even on failure (it's in `finally`); failure → exit `1` with stderr; `--format a4` reflected in injected `@page` CSS; `<head>` vs no-`<head>` injection paths.\n\n**Not covered by the earlier automated pass — CLI routing itself:**\n- `main()`'s subcommand dispatch (`db-new`/`db-mark`/`pdf-render`/`report-num`/`-h`/`--help` vs the fallback path).\n- Mode-word vs flag-passthrough splitting: `mode_words, extra = words[:i], words[i:]` at the first token starting with `-`.\n- `interactive` inference: bare `agent.py` → interactive; `-i`/`--interactive` anywhere in argv → interactive even with mode words.\n- `run_claude`: `os.execvp` when interactive vs `subprocess.call` with `CLAUDE_HEADLESS_FLAGS` when headless — needs both branches mocked.\n- `_chrome_bin`: `CHROME_PATH` env override → `shutil.which` candidates → hardcoded macOS app paths → `sys.exit` if none found.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_mark, cmd_report_num, _normalize_ats\nfrom pipeline import load_config\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef cfg(tmp_path):\n    db = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {db}\\n\")\n    return str(cfg_path)\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_em_dash_replaced_in_text(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>a\\u2014b</p>\")\n        assert \"a-b\" in html and counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n    def test_tag_attributes_untouched(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats('<div data-x=\"\\u2014\"></div>')\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in html and \"em-dash\" not in counts\n\n    def test_style_and_script_blocks_untouched(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<style>.a{content:'\\u2014'}</style><script>x='\\u2014'</script>\")\n        assert counts == {}\n\n    def test_no_changes_needed_returns_empty_counts(self):\n        assert _normalize_ats(\"<p>plain ascii</p>\")[1] == {}\n\n\nclass TestDbMark:\n    def test_invalid_watermark_exits_2_and_does_not_write(self, cfg, capsys):\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", cfg]) == 2\n        assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\n    def test_neither_watermark_nor_now_exits_2(self, cfg):\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", cfg]) == 2\n\n    def test_now_flag_sets_current_marker(self, cfg):\n        cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", cfg])\n        with Store(load_config(cfg)[\"db\"]) as s:\n            assert s.get_meta(\"last_scan\") is not None\n\n\nclass TestReportNum:\n    def test_first_call_prints_001(self, cfg, capsys):\n        cmd_report_num([\"-c\", cfg])\n        assert capsys.readouterr().out.strip() == \"001\"\n\n\nclass TestMainRouting:\n    def test_db_new_subcommand_dispatches(self, monkeypatch):\n        import agent\n        called = []\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"cmd_db_new\", lambda argv: called.append(argv) or 0)\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"agent.py\", \"db-new\", \"--limit\", \"5\"])\n        agent.main()\n        assert called == [[\"--limit\", \"5\"]]\n\n    def test_mode_words_stop_at_first_flag(self, monkeypatch):\n        import agent\n        captured = {}\n        def fake_run(mode_words, interactive, extra):\n            captured.update(mode_words=mode_words, interactive=interactive, extra=extra)\n            return 0\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"run_claude\", fake_run)\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"agent.py\", \"scan\", \"--dry-run\"])\n        agent.main()\n        assert captured[\"mode_words\"] == [\"scan\"]\n        assert captured[\"extra\"] == [\"--dry-run\"]\n\n    def test_interactive_flag_forces_interactive_with_mode_words(self, monkeypatch):\n        import agent\n        captured = {}\n        monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"run_claude\",\n            lambda mw, i, e: captured.update(interactive=i) or 0)\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"agent.py\", \"scan\", \"-i\"])\n        agent.main()\n        assert captured[\"interactive\"] is True\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. `cli.py` and integration — missing entirely\n\n- `main()`'s argparse wiring (`--config`, `--dry-run`) → `run_sync` call — trivial, zero coverage today.\n- No test exercises the **full chain** fetch → filter → dedup → notify with a realistic fixture (e.g. a recorded Greenhouse response run through `parse_greenhouse` → `filter_jobs` → `Store.diff` → assert the notifier sees the right job). Unit tests per stage won't catch a field-name mismatch *between* stages — that's exactly the gap the memory note about parallel-worker report collisions hints at as a systemic risk category.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\ndef test_main_passes_config_and_dry_run(monkeypatch):\n    import cli\n    captured = {}\n    monkeypatch.setattr(cli, \"run_sync\", lambda path, dry_run: captured.update(path=path, dry_run=dry_run))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"-c\", \"custom.yaml\", \"--dry-run\"])\n    cli.main()\n    assert captured == {\"path\": \"custom.yaml\", \"dry_run\": True}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Priority order\n\n1. **`models.py` + `filters.py`** — pure, cheap, highest logic-bug risk.\n2. **`store.py`** — dedup correctness is the tool's core value; in-memory SQLite makes it cheap.\n3. **`fetchers.py` parsers** — largest count of untested functions, most likely to silently break on vendor payload changes; even thin happy-path+empty-payload tests catch most regressions. `_request` retry logic guards every fetcher at once.\n4. **`notify.dispatch` isolation** — one test, guards an important resilience property.\n5. **`agent.py`** — `_normalize_ats`, `cmd_db_new`'s truncation/posted-days logic, and CLI routing are the riskiest hand-rolled pieces.\n6. **`pipeline.py`/`cli.py`** — thin orchestration, cover last; add one true end-to-end integration test here.\n",
